              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">March 25, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 1592</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Ramos<br/><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(Coauthor: Assembly Member Ward)<br/></i></font></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>January 15, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add Article<font color="#B30000"><strike> 1.8</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> 4</i></font> (commencing with Section<font color="#B30000"><strike> 528)</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> 570)</i></font> to Chapter 1 of Division 1 of the Public Resources Code, relating to state parks. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 1592, as amended, Ramos.
                          California Indian Heritage Center support organization.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law authorizes the Department of Parks and Recreation to enter into a statewide agreement with a park support organization to facilitate the implementation of reforms recommended by the Parks Forward Commission and to develop and secure expertise, services, resources, and projects that are not readily available to the state park system for specified purposes.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law provides for the department’s development of a California Indian Heritage Center for cultural preservation, learning and exchange, land stewardship, and a place to engage all visitors in celebrating the living cultures of California Native American tribes.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would authorize the department to enter into an agreement with a California Indian Heritage Center support organization, as defined, for the purpose of creating a
		collaborative partnership between California Native American tribes and the department to achieve specified purposes in support of the California Indian Heritage Center. The bill would require the California Indian Heritage Center support organization to be overseen by a board of directors, with designated membership, and led by a chief executive officer, as provided.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><caml:BillSection id="id_EFA75872-D936-4BDC-90FD-380BC7024493"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SECTION 1.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_ADDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:PRC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'1.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'1.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'4.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SPREAD||commencingWith: 570" xlink:type="locator">Article 1.8  (commencing with Section 528)  is  added to Chapter 1 of Division 1 of the
				<caml:DocName>Public Resources Code</caml:DocName>,  to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawHeading id="id_DD15B14F-3263-4272-99C5-553F8DB42DE3" type="ARTICLE"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>1.8.</caml:Num><caml:LawHeadingVersion id="id_E33A0D0B-165B-4A4B-A470-50BA8A6BA7A7"><caml:LawHeadingText/></caml:LawHeadingVersion></caml:LawHeading></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection></strike></font><div id="s20.39224115025156736"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SECTION 1.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Article 4 (commencing with Section 570) is added to Chapter 1 of Division 1 of the Public Resources Code, to read:</i></font></div><div><div><div id="id_912EA959-6724-48E8-9B49-4368C9684ECB"><div><h5 style="text-align:left;">
                Article
               4. California Indian Heritage Center Support Organization</h5></div></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>528.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>570.</i></font></h6> For purposes of this article, the following definitions apply:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(a) “Board” means the board of directors established pursuant to Section<font color="#B30000"><strike> 528.4.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> 570.4.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) “CIHC” means the California Indian Heritage Center established pursuant to Chapter 1.78 (commencing with Section 5097.999) of Division 5.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) “CIHC support organization” means a nonprofit organization established for the purpose of creating a collaborative partnership between California Native American tribes and the department in support of the CIHC.</div></p></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>528.2.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>570.2.</i></font></h6> The Legislature finds and declares both of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(a) In reflection of historical wrongs committed against California Native American tribes and in the spirit of truth and healing, the operations and programming of the CIHC located in West Sacramento must be meaningfully informed by and benefit California Native American<font color="#B30000"><strike> tribes,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> tribes</i></font> and serve as a place for sharing and
					 learning between tribes and the public.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) The unique relationship between California Native American tribes, tribal governments, and the department, as well as the shared vision and purpose of the CIHC, merits a special partnership uniquely established for this historic collaborative partnership.</div></p></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>528.4.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>570.4.</i></font></h6> (a) A CIHC support organization shall meet all of the following requirements:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Be exempt from taxation pursuant to Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Comply with the Supervision of Trustees and Fundraisers for Charitable Purposes Act (Article 7 (commencing with Section 12580) of Chapter 6 of Part 2 of Division 3 of Title 2 of the Government Code).</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Not be a state agency or body.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) Not directly manage state capital outlay projects.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) The department may enter into an agreement with a CIHC support organization to achieve all of the following purposes:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) To partner in the operation and programming of the CIHC to achieve the collective mission of establishing partnerships with California Native American tribes.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) To recruit, hire, and retain more diversity of CIHC staff with personal experience and knowledge of California Native American culture and history.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) To enter into staff-sharing agreements to use essential skills and abilities of state and nonstate employees, subject to all of the following requirements:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) State employees shall not be paid or otherwise compensated directly by the CIHC support organization.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) State employees shall not be directly supervised or managed by employees of the CIHC support organization.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) All<font color="#B30000"><strike> staff sharing</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> staff-sharing</i></font> agreements shall include<font color="#B30000"><strike> conflict of interest</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> conflict-of-interest</i></font> provisions for state employees that clearly outline roles and responsibilities to support ethical conduct, trust, and
					 transparency.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) To develop and engage new sources of nonstate public and private funding for the support of the CIHC, including donations and fundraising efforts, when appropriate.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(5) To apply for, receive, and expend state funds in support of the CIHC.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(6) To support ongoing capital improvement projects managed by the department.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(7) To provide financial stability and ethical integrity through oversight and accountability.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(8) To support marketing and communications activities that promote the programs, amenities, and resources of the CIHC.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(9) To support projects and programs that facilitate access and visitation and
					 enhance educational opportunities, especially for young and more diverse audiences.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(10) To establish, improve, and support the completion of projects that establish or improve CIHC visitor amenities and facilities.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) (1) The CIHC support organization shall be led by a chief executive officer who shall report to the board established pursuant to paragraph (2).</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) (A) The CIHC support organization shall be overseen by a board. The board shall consist of no more than 25 members, with at least 51 percent of the board’s members representing California Native American tribes.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) In addition to the members appointed pursuant to subparagraph (A), the following may serve as ex officio, nonvoting members of the
					 board to assist in providing effective communication and coordination of efforts between the department and the CIHC support organization.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(i) The Director of the Department of Parks and Recreation, or the director’s designee.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(ii) The Director of Finance, or the director’s designee.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(iii) The Tribal Affairs Secretary who leads the Governor’s Office of Tribal Affairs, or the secretary’s designee.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(d) The CIHC support organization’s charter and articles of incorporation, as approved by the California Indian Heritage Center task force established pursuant to Executive Order B-60-18 issued on December 20, 2018, shall set forth all other organizational terms of the CIHC support organization and the board not provided in this article, including, but not
					 limited to, the selection of the board’s members, organizational structures, responsibilities, terms of office, board member roles, meeting requirements, and other core governance details. The board may subsequently amend the CIHC support organization’s charter and articles of incorporation by majority vote.</div></p></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>528.6.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>570.6.</i></font></h6> (a) In order to advance the purposes described in subdivision (b) of Section<font color="#B30000"><strike> 528.4,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> 570.4,</i></font> an agreement between the department and the CIHC support organization pursuant to Section<font color="#B30000"><strike> 528.4</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> 570.4</i></font> shall, at a minimum, include<font color="#B30000"><strike> both</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
					 all</i></font> of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Clear goals and objectives.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Any commitments of oversight, staffing, and coordination that may be needed to accomplish the goals and objectives.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) A requirement that the department and the CIHC support organization annually hold a joint public meeting regarding the operation of the CIHC and the activities of the CIHC support organization.</div></i></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) (1) The department may develop and enter into supplementary agreements with the CIHC support organization for the purposes of securing any expertise, capacity, or financial resources that may be needed to identify,
					 plan, develop, or implement strategic initiatives and projects for the CIHC. These agreements may include, but are not limited to, grants, contracts, memoranda of understanding, staff-sharing agreements, leases, and rights of entry onto state park property.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Notwithstanding Part 2 (commencing with Section 10100) of Division 2 of the Public Contract Code, any agreements entered into by the department pursuant to this subdivision shall be under the control of the department and shall not be subject to any advertising or competitive bidding requirements applicable to public works or other public projects.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Any construction, alteration, demolition, installation, or repair work undertaken by or on behalf of the CIHC support organization for the CIHC on property owned by the state pursuant to this subdivision shall constitute a public work for purposes of Chapter 1 (commencing
					 with Section 1720) of Part 7 of Division 2 of the Labor Code.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) The Department of Finance shall have 60 days to review and approve or disapprove any agreement, or substantial amendment<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
					 to</i></font> an agreement, proposed under subdivision (a). Upon approval of the agreement or substantial amendment, the director may enter into supplementary agreements as authorized under subdivision (b).</div></p></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>528.8.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>570.8.</i></font></h6> This article does not commit, obligate, or require state funds to be provided in support of the CIHC support organization.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div><div align="center"><span class="CorrectionsSeparator">___________________</span></div><br/><br/><span class="CorrectionsHeading"><span class="Correction">
	 CORRECTIONS:</span><br/><span class="Correction">
	 Text—Page 2.</span><br/></span><div align="center"><span class="CorrectionsSeparator">___________________</span></div></div></body></html>
